ch.unibas.informatik.hs15.cs203.datarepository.api

Interface DataRepository


  • public interface DataRepository
    Interface for a programmatic access to the data repository. Exceptions are thrown if either the arguments are illegal (IllegalArgumentException) or the requested operation fails (RuntimeException). All thrown exceptions contain a human-readable message which explain for a user the reason which causes the exception.

    Methods with a ProgressListener argument have to report progress of copying data in either regular time intervals or chunks of bytes copied. Non of the methods of ProgressListener is invoked if the method arguments are invalid (that is, a IllegalArgumentException has to be thrown).

    Author:
    Franz-Josef Elmer

    • Method Detail

      • add

        MetaData add(File file,
           String description,
           boolean move,
           ProgressListener progressListener)
        Adds the specified file or folder to the repository as a new data set and returns its unique id.

        Note: In case of move == true

        Parameters:
        file - File or folder.
        description - An optional description of the data set. Can be null. If it is longer than 1000 characters or it contains ISO control characters an IllegalArgumentException is thrown.
        move - If true the file/folder will be moved into the repository. This works only if file/folder and repository folder are on the same physical file system. If this is not the case an exception is thrown. If false the file/folder will be copied (deep copy) into the repository folder.
        progressListener - Progress callback object. If move == true ProgressListener.progress(long, long) is called twice. First, with numberOfBytes == 0 and second with numberOfBytes == totalNumberOfBytes.
        Returns:
        meta data with unique identifier, number of files and total size.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - in the following cases:
        • file is null
        • file does not exists
        • file couldn't be moved
        • file is the repository folder or a file inside its hierarchy
        • description is invalid
        • progressListener is null

      • delete

        List<MetaData> delete(Criteria deletionCriteria)
        Deletes the data sets fulfilling the specified criteria. At least one criterion has to be specified.
        Parameters:
        deletionCriteria - Criteria of all data sets to be deleted have to fulfill.
        Returns:
        meta data of deleted data sets sorted by time stamps. Empty list of nothing exported.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - in the following cases:
        • deletionCriteria is null
        • all five criteria are null (i.e. all attributes of deletionCriteria are null)
        • deletionCriteria.getId() != null but no data set for the specified id exists

      • export

        List<MetaData> export(Criteria exportCriteria,
                    File target,
                    ProgressListener progressListener)
        Exports the data sets fulfilling the specified criteria to the specified target folder. If two data sets fulfilling the criteria have the same name an IllegalStateException is thrown.
        Parameters:
        exportCriteria - Criteria of all data sets to be exported have to fulfill.
        target - Destination folder for the data sets to be exported.
        progressListener - Progress callback object.
        Returns:
        meta data of exported data sets sorted by time stamps. Empty list if nothing exported.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - in the following cases:
        • exportCriteria is null
        • target is null
        • target isn't a folder
        • exportCriteria.getId() != null but no data set for the specified id exists
        • at least two of the data sets to be exported have the same name
        • at the destination is already a file/folder with same name as one of the data sets to be exported
        • progressListener is null

      • replace

        MetaData replace(String id,
               File file,
               String description,
               boolean move,
               ProgressListener progressListener)
        Replaces the data set specified by its id completely by the specified file or folder. If the description isn't specified the old description is kept.
        Parameters:
        id - Identifier of the data set to be replaced.
        file - File or folder.
        description - An optional description of the data set. Can be null. If it is longer than 1000 characters or it contains ISO control characters an exception is thrown.
        move - If true the file/folder will be moved into the repository. This works only if file/folder and repository folder are on the same physical file system. If this is not the case an exception is thrown. If false the file/folder will be copied (deep copy) into the repository folder.
        progressListener - Progress callback object. If move == true ProgressListener.progress(long, long) is called twice. First, with numberOfBytes == 0 and second with numberOfBytes == totalNumberOfBytes.
        Returns:
        meta data of replaced data set with new number of files and total size.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - in the following cases:
        • no data set for the specified id exists
        • file is null
        • file does not exists
        • file couldn't be moved
        • file is the repository folder or a file inside its hierarchy
        • description is invalid
        • progressListener is null

      • getMetaData

        List<MetaData> getMetaData(Criteria searchCriteria)
        Returns a list of meta data of all data sets fulfilling the criteria. The list is ordered by the time stamps.
        Parameters:
        searchCriteria - Criteria of all data sets to be listed.
        Returns:
        an empty list if no data set matches the criteria. List is sorted by time stamps.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if searchCriteria is null.
